description.narrative: Integrated Management of Childhood illness and Immunization services for Children, adolescent and pregnant women, especially in most vulnerable governorates and in humanitarian situations, are of high quality, sustainable and equitable.,which contributes to Child Health, Immunization, Immunization (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2024, all newborns, children, adolescents and women in Iraq access and equitably use affordable, high-impact health and nutrition services, especially the most vulnerable in humanitarian situations.
